post_text:
Message from the Keansburg Mayor and Council:

Dear Friends and Neighbors,

Presently there are 24 reported coronavirus cases in the Borough. Numbers being released to the public may be incorrect as the cases are being categorized by zip code. Our thoughts and prayers are with these residents and we wish them all a quick and complete recovery.

We want to assure you that our First Responders and Police Department are fully equipped and prepared to serve and protect our Citizens.

We encourage you to continue to practice social distancing and follow the personal safety guidelines as reported by the CDC and Governor Murphy.

At this time we ask that you support our business community who are providing take-out and delivery options.

Lastly we wish to acknowledge you efforts in complying with the Stay Home edicts. We are very proud that you are all doing your part to help beat this global health crisis.

Stay safe, stay HOME and be well!

post_text:
Good Morning All;

It is with deepest sadness that we announce that the 2020 Keansburg St. Patrick's Day Parade is being CANCELLED at this time due to the COVID-19 Coronavirus and the Governor's directive of no crowds of over 250 people.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause your group, but it is beyond our control. We hope that you will all continue to work with us in the future.

As of this moment the 2020 Memorial Day to honor our lost service members is still a go for Sunday May 17. We hope that you will join us for this parade and make it even bigger and better.

Sincerely and Best Wishes
George Hoff
Councilman
Borough of Keansburg

Keansburg FD Volunteer EMS
May 20, 2019 at 9:45 AM ¬∑

WE NEED YOUR HELP!!

Last night at approximately 1:30am our ambulance responded to a call in the area of Main St & Center Ave. Our crew left the area with the patient to the hospital shortly after. At 530am they went on another call and realized they left one of our medical bags at the previous call at Main and Center. When our police went back to the address to grab the bag for us the resident stated they left it on the curb thinking we would come right back for it. It was not there. We are hoping a good Samaritan grabbed and not the garbage truck. If anyone has any information or sees this bag please contact Keansburg Police at 732-787-0600. Thank you!

Note: This bag does not contain drugs.

This Saturday is the St. Patrick‚Äôs Parade. The parade route is as follows:

Begins at the new Police Station at 1:30pm.

Up Carr to Center

Down Center to Main

Down Main and ending at Keansburg Fire Company where there will be a parade party from 2:00 - 6:00 with corned beef and refreshments available for purchase.

There is NO PARKING anywhere along the parade route. Your vehicle MAY be subject to a summons and/or removal.

The weather is supposed to be fantastic - we hope to see everyone out enjoying the day!
